    {
      "id": "8ec1108d_cf1c30b2",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/impl/inventory/trustlevel/TrustLevelManager.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": null,
      "message": "legacy issues (that are getting worse now)\n1) when we talked about this feature we used the word 'device' for clarification and clearly distinguishing it from the 'dmi service' Whoever for consistency a 'device' in NCMP is a 'Cm Handle' and that is the term that should be sued in variabel names, method names and java dox!\n2) method names are too logn and have redundant words like 'handle' and 'of'. The names dont need to be sentences just keywords and relevant verbs wil do,\n\nso instead of handleRegistrationOfSomething just 'registerSomething' is much clearer...\n\nsee suggestions below",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2024-08-06 17:06:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
